  <annotation encoding="MathType-MTEF">MathType@MTEF@5@5@@400F@</annotation>
 </semantics></annotation-xml></semantics></math>.</p><p id="fs-id1618560">In theory, any chemical reaction can proceed in either direction under the right conditions. Reactants may synthesize into a product that is later decomposed. Reversibility is also a quality of exchange reactions. For instance, <math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="left"><semantics><mrow>
